  "doc_id": "38988",
  "text": "In our previous report, we noted that drowsiness was a common adverse event in the GEXR group (N = 26/30 versus 3/ 32 for placebo). Parents also reported mid-sleep awakening in 9 of 32 subjects taking GEXR compared to 2/32 for placebo [CITATION_1] . In clinical practice, the alpha 2 receptor agonizts, clonidine and guanfacine, are commonly used off-label to help children fall asleep [CITATION_2] . We included the CSHQ to assess the impact of GEXR on sleep. The results presented here do not support the use of GEXR as a sleep aid.",
